# AISDLC-421 — per-patch-id transcript-leaves files.
#
# Each PR's attestation-signing flow appends leaves to its OWN file at
# `.ai-sdlc/transcript-leaves/<patch-id>.jsonl`. Because every PR has a
# distinct patch-id (content-addressed via `git patch-id --stable`), two
# PRs writing to the same file is essentially impossible by construction.
#
# `merge=binary` is the defense-in-depth driver: if two PRs DID somehow
# land at the same patch-id (cherry-pick across branches, manual writes,
# etc.) and both modified the file, the rebase MUST surface as a hard
# conflict rather than silently union-merging. Silent union-merge would
# reorder leaves, which would invalidate the signed Merkle root because
# rootHash is computed over a SPECIFIC leaf sequence — a misleading
# downstream "rootHash mismatch" would surface instead of the actual
# upstream "two PRs collided on the same patch-id" failure.
#
# Rationale (hermetic test): see
# pipeline-cli/src/attestation/per-patch-id-rebase.test.ts.
.ai-sdlc/transcript-leaves/*.jsonl merge=binary
